 for the values of ordinary life. From this experience, an underground cultural movement was born. Rejecting idolatry, these relocated revolutionaries developed a new form of resistance that signaled a new era of enlightenment, culminating in the Democracy Wall movement of the late 1970s and the Tiananmen protest of 1989. Yang's final chapter on the politics of history and memory argues that contemporary memories of the Cultural Revolution are factionalized along these lines of political division, formed fifty years before.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aInterviewszChinazChongqing. 0aPolitical activistszChinazChongqingvInterviews. 0aPolitical violencezChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical violencezChinazChongqingxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial movementszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial movementszChinazChongqingxHistoryy20th century. 0aUrban-rural migrationxPolitical aspectszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aYouthxPolitical activityzChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aYouthxPolitical activityzChinazChongqingxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063857808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2016z9783110485189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/yang1496440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231520485423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231520485/original  a978-3-11-063857-8  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV